Detailed Description

cvmx_agl_gmx_tx::_clk

AGL_GMX_TX_CLK = RGMII TX Clock Generation Register

Notes: Normal Programming Values: (1) RGMII, 1000Mbs (AGL_GMX_PRT_CFG[SPEED]==1), CLK_CNT == 1 (2) RGMII, 10/100Mbs (AGL_GMX_PRT_CFG[SPEED]==0), CLK_CNT == 50/5 (3) MII, 10/100Mbs (AGL_GMX_PRT_CFG[SPEED]==0), CLK_CNT == 1

RGMII Example: Given a 125MHz PLL reference clock... CLK_CNT == 1 ==> 125.0MHz TXC clock period (8ns* 1) CLK_CNT == 5 ==> 25.0MHz TXC clock period (8ns* 5) CLK_CNT == 50 ==> 2.5MHz TXC clock period (8ns*50)

Additionally reset when MIX<prt>_CTL[RESET] is set to 1.
